FT  15 JUN 94 / International Company News: Improvement at RH Macy
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FRANK MCGURTY
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK.
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
RH Macy, the US retailer struggling to emerge from Chapter 11 bankruptcy
protection, said it was encouraged by the steady improvement in its
underlying performance in the third quarter, writes Frank McGurty in New
York.
The department store chain, which is expected to submit a reorganisation
plan to a federal court at the end of this month, announced a 32 per cent
jump in earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortisation to
Dollars 34.9m for the three months to the end of April, against Dollars
26.5m a year earlier. However, the net loss was Dollars 157.3m, or Dollars
97.28 a share, against a Dollars 227.9m deficit recorded in the year-earlier
quarter.
For the nine months, Macy posted a net loss of Dollars 217m, or Dollars
132.82 a share, against a shortfall of Dollars 354.9m, or Dollars 219.49, a
year earlier.
