<HEADLINE>
FT  15 JUN 94 / UK Company News: Inflation culture limiting projects says
BoS chief
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Bruce Pattullo, governor of the Bank of Scotland, said yesterday that the
'slow change in Britain's inflation prone culture' was limiting the number
of new investment projects being launched by large UK companies. They were
still seeking high investment despite low inflation.
At the annual meeting in Edinburgh Mr Pattullo said 'the reluctance by
management to adjust downwards the returns which they seek on new projects
means that the new jobs which would be created by new investment
announcements will be delayed'.
