<HEADLINE>
FT  15 JUN 94 / Observer: US bonding
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The word from Wall Street is that the Clinton administration has announced
plans for a new, three-tranche US government bond issue.
The first tranche is the 'Gore' - No interest. The second is the
'Stephanopoulos' - No maturity. The third is the 'Billary' - No principal. A
rumoured fourth tranche, to be used only in emergencies, is the 'Paula' - No
date.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>USZ  United States of America.
</CN>
