<HEADLINE>
FT  15 JUN 94 / Observer: Gloom speaks
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
John Major's renewed interest in seeing British MPs working 'sensible hours'
is not to the taste of some members of the House of Lords.
The peers have recently been burning the midnight oil on the bill to
privatise British Coal. Nearly nine hours after making the initial speech
from the Labour front bench on Monday, Lord Morris said he was glad the
House did not meet at 9 o'clock in the morning. 'I get better as the light
gets darker,' he confessed.
Rather like mushrooms, really.
