FT  15 JUN 94 / Observer: Party pooper
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Talking of dogs, what do we make of Labour MP Ken Livingstone's support for
the 'Scoop that poop' campaign which he helped launch in Battersea Park last
weekend?
The aim is to 'persuade owners to clear up after Britain's 7.5m dogs' and
the sponsors, dog-food manufacturers James Wellbeloved &amp; Co, wanted a tame
MP to pose for the cameras, because fouling by dogs is an issue upon which
MPs receive more mail than any other.
Another sign, perhaps, that the Labour leftwinger is not taking seriously
his other campaign - to collect colleagues' signatures for his candidacy in
Labour's leadership race?
