FT  15 JUN 94 / Guidelines on wind farms
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The UK wind energy industry is to establish best practice guidelines to
promote the development of wind farms. These will cover site selection,
environmental assessment, and community consultation and involvement.
The industry is responding to mounting controversy over the rapid
development of wind farms, often on prominent sites and against local
opposition.
Mr Ian Mays, chairman of the British Wind Energy Association, said he
believed that 'with care and sensitivity the potential of wind energy to
provide a significant, clean, sustainable and popular contribution to our
energy needs will be realised'.
