<TEXT>
New procedures for handling complaints by investors are to be introduced by
the Securities and Investments Board, Mr Anthony Nelson, economic secretary
to the Treasury, announced last night, Ivor Owen writes.
He told the Commons the appointment of a complaints commissioner was one of
the proposals under discussion.
