<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JUN 94 / World Stock Markets: Equity Markets
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The implications of the European elections for equity markets will be felt
this week. It was good news for Austria, which also voted at the weekend in
favour of joining the European Union; the Vienna market was the best
performer in local currency terms among the constituents of the FT-Actuaries
World index. The Austrian decision could have a positive short-term effect
for those Scandinavian markets which are due to vote on union this autumn,
although Unibank Securities reports that the 'no' vote campaign continues to
lead polls in both Sweden and Norway.
