<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JUN 94 / World Stock Markets: Brazil
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Equities in Sao Paulo dropped from earlier highs to end a net 2.4 per cent
down in light trading dominated by a struggle between longs and shorts prior
to this week's futures index settlement. The market was 2 per cent up at
midday.
The Bovespa index lost 735 points at 29,469, while turnover totalled Cr343bn
(Dollars 159m).
The futures index settlement is scheduled for tomorrow, while options
settlement takes place on June 20.
