FT  14 JUN 94 / International Company News: Dutch Alcoa chief sees squeeze
on aluminium groups
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   DRUNEN, THE NETHERLANDS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Smaller west European aluminium companies will be increasingly squeezed by
east European rivals and global operators in their own market, said Mr Berry
Bemelmans, president of Alcoa Nederland, Reuter reports from Drunen, the
Netherlands.
Mr Bemelmans said that companies needed to establish a significant presence
in the key packaging, aerospace or transportation aluminium sectors to
ensure their survival.
A further challenge would come as Russian producers moved from exports of
ingots and extrusions to products with greater added value.
Mr Bemelmans said Alcoa Nederland, through its ownership by Aluminum Company
of America, was the first western company to establish a significant
presence in the east European aluminium market.
