FT  14 JUN 94 / International Company News: Moulinex losses deepen to
FFr598m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN RIDDING
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Moulinex, the French household appliances group, suffered a net loss of
FFr598m (Dollars 104.54m) in fiscal 1993, a sharp increase from losses of
FFr41m the previous year.
The company, which is in the process of a substantial refinancing and
restructuring programme, said the results for the year to the end of March
included a FFr185m restructuring charge, a FFr132m exceptional charge
relating to a write-down of R&amp;D investments and a FFr170m charge relating to
product and customer risks.
Moulinex said negotiations with Euris, an investment consortium which is
planning to take a substantial stake in the company, could be completed by
the end of this month. The refinancing package includes a FFr1bn rights
issue, the details of which are being finalised.
In addition to the restructuring charges, last year's results were also
affected by recession in many of the group's principal markets in western
Europe and the impact of exchange rate fluctuations in Italy, Spain and the
UK.
Moulinex said that it had responded to the more difficult economic
environment by cutting inventory levels and reducing capital expenditure to
FFr230m, compared with FFr569m in the previous year.
